history.content:
I don't know who the professor is for this fall, but I took 70 in Spring 2016 and know that it was curved in such a way that most of the class received a solid B. If a B+ is what you need, I would recommend erring on the side of caution and making that your only technical for the semester.

With that said, if you feel confident in your ability to get a B+ alongside another technical, by all means take 16A alongside 70. I just feel like if I were in your position I would want to give myself as much time as possible to focus on the class I need to declare.

The professors for 70 are currently listed as Rao and Ramchandran. Having taken classes with both, I must say neither are likely to "go easy" but they are amazing profs!

These are 2 classes that students report are very difficult. Taking them together may prove to be a heavy time commitment. Perhaps better to space these out a bit. We have also learned from faculty that EE 16A and B are great prep for CS 70!

children.subject: I took EE16A along with CS70 and it was manageable but I think that's because I've also taken 54 and had a pretty solid linear algebra background. I ended up spending the majority of my time on CS70 and the back-to-back problem sets (70 problem sets are usually due on Fridays and 16a problem sets are usually due on Mondays) did get kind of tiring. It's definitely doable (I was also worried about doing both like you are) but it will be a long semester
